{
  "doc_id": "12589",
  "text": "Septins are found as heteromeric complexes that can assemble in larger filaments [CITATION_1] . All septins have in common a GTP binding domain that consists of the binding motifs G1 (P-loop), G3, and G4. Most septins contain a predicted coiled-coil domain at the C terminus [CITATION_2] . In many cases, septins seem to serve as a scaffold or matrix for other proteins [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . Therefore, progress in understanding septins' functions will depend in part on identifying the proteins with which the septins interact.",
